<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A top official at the Bank of England said it was 'quite likely' that the Covid-hit economy would need more stimulus to offset what may be years of social distancing and the growing risk of post-Brexit trade barriers. </p>

<p>Stimulus: The Bank has already cut interest rates to a record low of 0.1 per cent and ramped up its money-printing programme by £300billion</p>

<p>The Bank has already cut interest rates to a record low of 0.1 per cent and ramped up its money-printing programme by £300billion. </p>

<p>But Michael Saunders considered it 'quite likely additional monetary easing will be appropriate'.</p>
